newborn's%20hip%20bone%20was%20found%20in%20a%20French%20cave.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20bone%20could%20mean%20modern%20humans%20shared%20the%20cave%20with%20Neanderthals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20finding%20hints%20humans%20and%20Neanderthals%20may%20have%20a%20mysterious%20common%20culture.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20tiny%2040%2C000-year-old%20human%20hip%20bone%20found%20in%20a%20French%20cave%20could%20overhaul%20what%20we%20know%20about%20how%20humans%20interacted%20with%20Neanderthals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20human%20bone%20was%20found%20in%20a%20cave%20at%20the%20center%20of%20a%20debate%20about%20Neanderthal%20culture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20we%20have%20the%20association%20in%20a%20single%20year%20of%20two%20different%20human%20lineages%3A%20Neanderthals%20and%20anatomically%20modern%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20expert%20Bruno%20Maureille%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaureille%20is%20an%20author%20of%20the%20study%20about%20the%20hip%20bone%2C%20and%20an%20archaeologist%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Bordeaux.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20finding%20suggests%20that%20early%20humans%20and%20Neanderthals%20may%20have%20shared%20the%20cave%20at%20the%20same%20time%20%E2%80%94%20and%20possibly%20lived%20together%2C%20said%20Maureille.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20raises%20a%20controversial%20hypothesis%3A%20that%20modern%20humans%20and%20Neanderthals%20shared%20the%20mysterious%20Ch%C3%A2telperronien%20culture%2C%20which%20has%20long%20baffled%20scientists.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWho%20is%20responsible%20for%20the%20Ch%C3%A2telperronien%20culture%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Grotte%20du%20Renne%20cave%20in%20Arcy-sur-Cure%2C%20southwestern%20France%2C%20is%20a%20particularly%20important%20site%20for%20our%20burgeoning%20understanding%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneanderthal-oldest-cave-drawings-found-france-2023-6%5C%22%3ENeanderthal%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C