C%22%20height%3D%5C%22538%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Grotte%20du%20Renne%20in%20France%20is%20the%20hub%20of%20debate%20about%20Neanderthal%20culture%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Maps%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20or%20not%20these%20two%20groups%20overlapped%20has%20been%20a%20point%20of%20contention.%20That's%20in%20part%20because%2042%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneanderthal-extinction-earth-magnetic-poles-flip-climate-change-2021-2%5C%22%3EEarth's%20magnetic%20poles%20flipped%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20is%20this%20important%20because%20it%20may%20have%20brought%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneanderthal-extinction-earth-magnetic-poles-flip-climate-change-2021-2%5C%22%3Eglobal%20climate%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20have%20helped%20edge%20out%20Neanderthals%2C%20but%20the%20flip%20may%20also%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Fmodern-humans-and-neanderthals-may-have-overlapped-shared-culture-western-europe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupercharged%20the%20carbon-14%20isotope%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20which%20has%20made%20carbon%20dating%20around%20that%20time%20particularly%20tricky%20to%20interpret%2C%20Science%20Magazine%20previously%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20the%20Ch%C3%A2telperronian%20culture%20is%20so%20important.%20Some%20believe%20Neanderthals%20were%20the%20artisans%20of%20this%20culture.%20Others%20think%20modern%20humans%20brought%20the%20tools%20with%20them%2C%20and%20Neanderthals%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20finding%20offers%20weight%20to%20another%20hypothesis%3A%20early%20modern%20humans%20and%20Neanderthals%20may%20have%20cooked%20it%20up%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20modern%20human%20baby%20bone%20among%20the%20Neanderthals%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20one%20bone%20fragment%2C%20a%20hip%20bone%20from%20a%20newborn%20baby%20that%20had%20gone%20unnoticed%20among%20Neanderthal%20fossils%20collected%20from%20the%20cave%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221673%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20picture%20shows%20a%20romboid-shaped%20white%20bone%20fragment%20seen%20from%20the%20front%20and%20back.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e7316352bc2d001990ff6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22836%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20picture%20of%20the%20front%20and%20back%20of%20the%20hip%20bone%20fragment%20found%20in%20the%20Grotte%20du%20Renne.%3Cp%3EGicqueau%2C%20A.%20et%20al%2C%20Sci%20Rep%2013%2C%2012682%20(2023).%20https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41598-023-39767-2%20(CC%20BY%204.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20fossils%20were%20found%20in%20a%20layer%20of%20dirt%20dated%20between%20about%2040%2C799%20to%2042%2C300%20years%20ago%2C%20which%20puts%20them%20in%20that%20controversial%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaureille%20and%20his%20colleagues%20were%20intrigued%20by%20this%20one%20hip%20bone.%20It%20was%20slender%20and%20looked%20closer%20to%20the%20anatomy%20of%20a%20modern%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20did%20a%20wide-ranging%20analysis%20comparing%20the%20hip%20bone%20to%20that%20of%20two%20contemporary%20Neanderthal%20babies%20and%20that%20of%2032%20modern-day%20human%20babies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20work%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20confirm%20their%20inkling%3A%20this%20particular%20hip%20bone%20was%20not%20from%20a%20Neanderthal%20but%20likely%20came%20from%20an%20early%20modern%20human%20lineage.%20The%20findings%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D1c1690a3e4fd0f87a2c0b120ce1e0b606ada65c7247a4098486110ffabc912d9%26postID%3D64e5ee8644625f836ffab927%26postSlug%3D40000-year-bone-hints-humans-neanderthals-shared-cave-culture-2023-8%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-023-39767-2%253Futm_medium%253Daffiliate%2526utm_source%253Dcommission_junction%2526utm_campaign%253DCONR_PF018_ECOM_GL_PHSS_ALWYS_DEEPLINK%2526utm_content%253Dtextlink%2526utm_term%253DPID100052172%2526CJEVENT%253D50c33c03426111ee81a600d50a18ba72%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20Scientific%20Reports%20on%20August%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20the%20most%20ancient%20ilea%20that%20we%20know%20for%20all%20the%20history%20of%20humanity%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Maureille%2C%20using%20the%20scientific%20name%20for%20a%20hip%20bone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20then%20is%3A%20what%20is%20this%20human%20bone%20doing%20mixed%20in%20with%20Neanderthal%20remains%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20it%20proves%20that%20humans%20were%20indeed%20there%20all%20along%2C%20and%20they%20were%20the%20ones%20who%20originated%20the%20Ch%C3%A2telperronian%20culture.%20For%20others%2C%20the%20human%20bone%20was%20simply%20misplaced%20among%20the%20Neanderthal%20remains%20when%20it%20was%20collected%20and%20stored.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Maureille%20thinks%20the%20%26quot%3Bsimplest%26quot%3B%20explanation%20is%20that%20humans%20and%20Neanderthals%20were%20either%20mixed%20together%20or%20lived%20side-by-side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20be%20in%20line%20with%20another%20recent%20finding%20uncovered%20about%203%2C000%20miles%20away%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenisovans-neanderthals-humans-occupied-denisova-cave-siberia-2021-6%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20mountains%20of%20Siberia.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Research%20there%20suggests%20modern%20humans%20shared%20a%20cave%20with%20Neanderthals%20and%20Denisovans%20about%2045%2C000%20years%20ago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20because%20both%20were%20able%20to%20understand%20the%20industry%20of%20the%20other%2C%20Maureille%20thinks%20it%20would%20make%20sense%20that%20Neanderthals%20and%20humans%20would%20likely%20have%20shared%20the%20Ch%C3%A2telperronian%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F40000-year-bone-hints-humans-neanderthals-shared-cave-culture-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692878627000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e72df8a7adf7001906cf83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F40000-year-bone-hints-humans-neanderthals-shared-cave-culture-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20hip%20bone%20was%20found%20in%20the%20Grotte%20du%20Renne%20in%20France%2C%20a%20cave%20considered%20by%20some%20to%20be%20the%20last%20bastion%20of%20Neanderthal%20culture%20in%20Western%20Europe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Marianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F40000-year-bone-hints-humans-neanderthals-shared-cave-culture-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22United%20Airlines%20settles%20for%20%2430%20million%20with%20the%20family%20of%20a%20quadriplegic%20man%20who%20was%20left%20brain%20damaged%20after%20he%20was%20'violently'%20moved%20while%20deplaning%2C%20lawsuit%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224079%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22United%20Airlines%20plane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b40090f9a25900194779bf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222424%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20United%20Airlines%20plane.%3Cp%3EThierry%20Monasse%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUnited%20Airlines%20agreed%20to%20settle%20a%20lawsuit%20for%20%2430%20million%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20relates%20to%20a%20man%20in%20a%20wheelchair%20who%20was%20left%20brain%20damaged%20and%20unable%20to%20speak%2C%20court%20documents%20show.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENJ%20Foster%20went%20into%20cardiac%20arrest%20after%20being%C2%A0%26quot%3Bviolently%26quot%3B%20moved%20while%20deplaning%2C%20the%20suit%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUnited%20Airlines%20has%20settled%20a%20lawsuit%20with%20the%20family%20of%20a%20man%20in%20a%20wheelchair%2C%20who%20was%20left%20brain-damaged%20after%20suffering%20a%20heart%20attack%20when%20ground%20staff%20contracted%20by%20United%20helped%20him%20deplane%2C%20court%20filings%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20settlement%20is%20worth%20%2430%20million%2C%20around%20%2412%20million%20of%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20pay%20for%20legal%20costs%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Faerospace-defense%2Funited-airlines-30-mln-settlement-with-quadriplegic-mans-family-2023-08-23%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20first%20reported%20the%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECourt%20filings%20viewed%20by%20Insider%20show%20a%20settlement%20was%20disclosed%20on%20Tuesday%20after%20one%20day%20of%20trial%2C%20ending%20a%20legal%20action%20that%20began%20more%20than%20four%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENJ%20Foster%2C%20a%20quadriplegic%2021-year-old%20who%20had%20been%20using%20a%20wheelchair%2C%20ventilator%2C%20and%20tracheal%20tube%2C%20was%20with%20his%20family%20returning%20from%20a%20funeral%20in%20February%202019.%20Per%20court%20documents%2C%20the%20incident%20occurred%20when%20the%20family%20was%20disembarking%20a%20United%20Express%20flight%20from%20Houston%2C%20Texas%20to%20Monroe%20Airport%20in%20Louisiana%20%E2%80%93%20this%20was%20the%20second%20leg%20of%20their%20journey.%20United%20Express%20is%20part%20of%20United%20Airlines.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20says%20that%20typically%2C%20four%20to%20six%20people%20helped%20Foster%20deplane%2C%20but%20only%20one%20flight%20attendant%20was%20present%20initially.%20The%20agent%20called%20for%20assistance%20and%20a%20woman%20who%20identified%20herself%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsupervisor%26quot%3B%20turned%20up%20with%20an%20aisle%20chair.%20It%20is%20not%20clear%20from%20the%20filing%20whether%20this%20agent%20was%20employed%20directly%20by%20the%20airline%20or%20subcontracted.%20After%20the%20family%20protested%20and%20said%20they%20would%20need%20additional%20help%2C%20the%20agent%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BFine.%20Do%20it%20yourself%2C%20then%20...%20I'm%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20baggage%20claim%20handler%20employed%20by%20one%20of%20United's%20contractors%20then%20secured%20Foster%20into%20the%20aisle%20chair%20with%20one%20cross-chest%20restraint%2C%20even%20though%20additional%20leg%20and%20lap%20straps%20were%20previously%20used%2C%20per%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFoster's%20aisle%20chair%20was%20%26quot%3Baggressively%20pushed%2C%26quot%3B%20causing%20him%20to%20twice%20slip%20over%20the%20side%20of%20the%20chair%20before%20being%20propped%20up%20by%20his%20father.%20According%20to%20the%20court%20filing%2C%20the%20contracted%20agent%20then%20%26quot%3Bforcefully%26quot%3B%20pushed%20the%20chair%2C%20making%20it%20move%20%26quot%3Bviolently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFoster%20then%20told%20his%20mother%20he%20couldn't%20breathe%2C%20and%20she%20called%20for%20a%20doctor.%20Another%20agent%2C%20employed%20by%20United%20and%20working%20at%20the%20airport%20gate%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3Bgiggled%26quot%3B%20and%20told%20the%20doctor%20that%20no%20help%20was%20needed%20before%20Foster%20went%20into%20cardiac%20arrest%2C%20the%20suit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20dad%20performed%20CPR%2C%20Foster%20arrived%20at%20the%20hospital%20in%20a%20coma%20having%20suffered%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%26quot%3B%20brain%20damage%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20oxygen%2C%20per%20the%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20aged%2026%2C%20Foster%20cannot%20speak%20or%20eat%20solid%20foods%2C%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20live%20to%20age%2031%2C%20down%20from%2039%20before%20the%20incident%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20top%20priority%20is%20to%20provide%20a%20safe%20journey%20for%20all%20our%20customers%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20require%20additional%20assistance%20or%20the%20use%20of%20a%20wheelchair%2C%26quot%3B%20United%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20seen%20by%20Reuters.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20pleased%20to%20share%20that%20this%20matter%20has%20settled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnited%20Airlines%20declined%20to%20comment%20when%20contacted%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-30-million-settlement-man-left-brain-damaged-deplaning-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692878535000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dc0f2f4ef9f30019f7ad96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-30-million-settlement-man-left-brain-damaged-deplaning-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22NJ%20Foster%20was%20left%20brain-damaged%20after%20suffering%20a%20heart%20attack%20when%20ground%20staff%20contracted%20by%20United%20helped%20him%20deplane.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40insider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-30-million-settlement-man-left-brain-damaged-deplaning-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Subway%20agrees%20to%20sell%20itself%20to%20Roark%20Capital%20at%20%249%20bn%20valuation%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692878450000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2019-06%2F29%2Ffull%2F1561829052-1615.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsubway-agrees-to-se