C%22%20height%3D%5C%221249%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVacant%20land%20in%20the%20Tucson%2C%20Arizona%20desert.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Van%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWilliam%20Gordon%20bought%20a%20lot%20in%20Tucson%20in%201999%20with%20plans%20to%20build%20his%20retirement%20home%20on%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20March%202023%2C%20the%20lot%20was%20sold%20for%20%24200%2C000%20by%20someone%20who%20Gordon%20said%20impersonated%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20buyers%20of%20the%20property%20were%20refunded%20but%20Gordon%20had%20to%20fight%20to%20get%20his%20property%20back.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202023%2C%20William%20Gordon%20received%20a%20letter%20in%20the%20mail%20from%20his%20title%20company%20congratulating%20him%20on%20the%20%24200%2C000%20sale%20of%20his%20Tucson%2C%20Arizona%2C%20property.%20The%20catch%3A%20He%20hadn't%20listed%20it%20for%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20noticed%20almost%20immediately%20that%20the%20congratulatory%20letter%20was%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20noticed%20the%20last%20four%20digits%20of%20the%20social%20security%20number%20were%20not%20mine%20and%20the%20address%20was%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20the%20mail%20shouldn't%20have%20even%20gotten%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%2C%2065%2C%20bought%20the%20undeveloped%2C%203%201%2F3-acre%20property%20in%201999%20for%20%2476%2C500%2C%20Pima%20County%20property%20records%20show.%20He's%20been%20paying%20regular%20mortgage%20payments%20on%20the%20land%20and%20had%20around%20%249%2C000%20left%20to%20pay%20on%20the%20loan%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20is%20one%20of%20many%20property%20owners%20that%20have%20been%20on%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20real-estate-related%20fraud.%20In%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fbi.gov%2Fcontact-us%2Ffield-offices%2Fboston%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Ffbi-warns-of-spike-in-rental-and-real-estate-scams%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E11%2C578%20people%20in%20the%20US%20reported%20losing%20a%20total%20of%20%24350%2C328%2C166%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20real-estate%20scams%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FBI's%20Internet%20Crime%20Complaint%20Center%20%E2%80%94%20a%2064%25%20increase%20from%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHome%20title%20theft%20%E2%80%94%20a%20crime%20where%20someone%20steals%20a%20homeowner's%20identity%20to%20take%20ownership%20of%20a%20property%20%E2%80%94%20leaves%20property%20owners%2C%20like%20Gordon%2C%20without%20many%20options%20for%20quick%20reconciliation.%20And%20it's%20been%20happening%20with%20greater%20regularity%20in%20recent%20years.%20In%20Gordon's%20case%2C%20he%20was%20pulled%20in%20many%20directions%20over%20countless%20phone%20calls%2C%20and%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20getting%20a%20straight%20answer%20on%20how%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20county%20said%2C%20all%20you%20have%20to%20do%20is%20just%20undo%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20nobody%20seemed%20to%20know%20how%20to%20undo%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20breakdown%20in%20responsibility%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20noticed%20a%20number%20of%20red%20flags%20in%20the%20congratulatory%20letter%20he%20received%20from%20the%20title%20company%20that%20he%20said%20they%20should%20have%20noticed%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20several%20really%20odd%20things%20that%20had%20been%20ignored%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20notary%20that%20they%20used%20was%20five-and-a-half%20hours%20away%20in%20an%20entirely%20different%20county%20from%20where%20the%20documents%20were%20signed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20lives%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20but%20the%20warranty%20deed%20recorded%20by%20the%20county%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20which%20was%20reviewed%20by%20Insider%20%E2%80%94%20had%20%26quot%3BArizona%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BPima%26quot%3B%20crossed%20out%20and%20replaced%20by%20%26quot%3BTexas%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BBexar%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20county%20almost%20900%20miles%20from%20Tucson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20not%20in%20Texas%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20prove%20that%20I%20was%20in%20Arizona%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20paperwork%20was%20signed%20by%20a%20notary%20in%20Texas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20who%20impersonated%20Gordon%2C%20but%20the%20notary%20stamp%20gave%20the%20name%20of%20%26quot%3BPenny%20Davis%26quot%3B%20of%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20spoke%20with%20Title%20Security%20Agency%2C%20the%20Arizona%20company%20that%20handled%20Gordon's%20title%20work%20when%20he%20purchased%20the%20property%20in%201999.%20(Note%3A%20The%20current%20entity%20came%20under%20new%20ownership%20in%202020%20after%20being%20acquired%20by%20First%20American%20Financial.)%20Gordon%20said%20they%20quickly%20realized%20someone%20was%20impersonating%20him.%20They%20directed%20him%20to%20his%20county%20recorder%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhose%20job%20it%20is%20to%20record%20and%20index%20documents%20for%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pima%20Recorder's%20Office%20told%20Gordon%20that%20they%20record%20documents%2C%20not%20verify%20them%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20sent%20him%20back%20to%20the%20title%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPima%20County%20Recorder%20Gabriella%20C%C3%A1zares-Kelly%20told%20Insider%20that%20she%20wasn't%20sure%20why%20the%20title%20company%20referred%20Gordon%20to%20her%2C%20saying%20the%20recorder's%20office%20is%20essentially%20a%20library.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20rely%20on%20title%20companies%2C%20on%20notaries%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20why%20they%20are%20required%20to%20have%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20because%20it%20is%20ultimately%20up%20to%20those%20companies%20to%20have%20the%20safeguards%20to%20ensure%20that%20they're%20dealing%20with%20the%20correct%20property%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotaries%20and%20real-estate%20agents%20usually%20confirm%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20parties%20involved%20in%20a%20transaction%20while%20title%20companies%20confirm%20ownership%20of%20the%20land%2C%20but%20according%20to%20Gordon%2C%20none%20of%20that%20happened%20before%20his%20land%20was%20sold.%20He%20was%20miffed%20that%20a%20document%20as%20crucial%20as%20a%20deed%20would%20not%20have%20a%20rigorous%20verification%20process%20for%20identification%2C%20he%20said.%20Title%20Security%20Agency%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20go%20and%20cash%20a%20check%20in%20a%20bank%20for%20%2420%20without%20two%20forms%20of%20identification%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20you're%20doing%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20financial%20transactions%2C%20and%20you%20have%20zero%20processes%20or%20feel%20any%20responsibility%20to%20confirm%20identities%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBrokerages%20are%20trying%20to%20stop%20fraud%20before%20it's%20too%20late%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EReal-estate%20agents%20in%20Arizona%20have%20seen%20a%20rise%20in%20fraud%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20for%20vacant%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20last%20three%20or%20four%20months%20we've%20seen%20a%20huge%20uptick%2C%20and%20it%20caught%20everybody%20by%20surprise%2C%26quot%3B%20Eric%20Gibbs%2C%20the%20designated%20broker%20for%20Realty%20ONE%20Group%20Integrity%2C%20said%20to%20Insider%20about%20title%20fraud.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20saying%20it%20never%20happened%20before%2C%20but%20not%20like%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGibbs%20didn't%20represent%20the%20buyer%20in%20Gordon's%20case%2C%20but%20his%20brokerage%20did.%20He%20told%20Insider%20that%20in%20this%20instance%2C%20the%20seller%20was%20found%20out%20to%20be%20fraudulent%20soon%20after%20the%20deal%20closed%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Cases%20like%20these%2C%20Gibbs%20said%2C%20are%20getting%20harder%20to%20sniff%20out.%20He%20told%20Insider%20he%20spoke%20with%20a%20broker%20that%20had%20four%20fraudulent%20incidents%20in%20one%20day.%20But%20Gibbs%20has%20instituted%20measures%20within%20his%20own%20firm%20%E2%80%94%20like%20asking%20for%20copies%20of%20photo%20IDs%20and%20having%20Zoom%20meetings%20with%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20to%20minimize%20fraud%20in%20vacant-land%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20situation%20going%20on%2C%20not%20only%20here%20but%20other%20places%2C%20where%20deed%20fraud%20is%20on%20the%20rise%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20trying%20to%20get%20a%20handle%20on%20how%20we%20can%20minimize%20the%20risk%2C%20because%20the%20people%20that%20are%20doing%20the%20fraud%20have%20gotten%20very%2C%20very%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Murtaugh%20%E2%80%94%20the%20CEO%20and%20designated%20broker%20for%20Realty%20Executives%20Arizona%20Territory%2C%20which%20brokered%20the%20sale%20of%20Gordon's%20property%20%E2%80%94%20says%20he's%20adopted%20a%20new%20procedure%20after%20seeing%20what%20Gordon%20went%20through.%20He%20now%20sends%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20property%20that%20must%20be%20signed%20by%20the%20seller%20and%20returned%2C%20in%20order%20to%20confirm%20their%20identity.%20But%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20question%20of%20who%20the%20responsibility%20to%20catch%20fraud%20falls%20to%20is%20still%20hazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20question%20is%2C%20who's%20got%20the%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20Murtaugh%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIs%20it%20the%20title%20company%3F%20Is%20it%20the%20agents%3F%20I%20don't%20think%20anybody%20knows%20that%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGordon%20got%20his%20land%20back%2C%20but%20not%20without%20a%20cost%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20hired%20a%20legal%20team%20%E2%80%94%20that%20he%20has%20since%20dismissed%20%E2%80%94%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20get%20his%20land%20back%20at%20a%20cost%20of%C2%A0%20around%20%249%2C000.%20He%20ultimately%20got%20his%20property%20back%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20easy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20buyers%20were%20refunded%20their%20%24200%2C000%20from%20Old%20Republic%20Title%20Insurance%2C%20the%20title%20insurance%20company%20they%20used%20in%20the%20transaction%2C%20they%20signed%20a%20quitclaim%20deed%20which%20relinquished%20the%20right%20to%20ownership%20of%20Gordon's%20property%20and%20granted%20the%20county%20the%20ability%20to%20transfer%20the%20title%20back%20into%20Gordon's%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sounds%20easy%20enough%2C%20but%20Gordon%20said%20he%20ran%20into%20a%20predicament%20with%20the%20title%20insurance%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOld%20Republic%20Title%20Insurance%20paid%20off%20Gordon's%20remaining%20mortgage%20balance%20and%20property%20taxes%20during%20the%20sales%20process%20and%20demanded%20he%20pay%20them%20back%20%2411%2C000%2C%20Gordon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGordon%20ended%20up%20taking%20money%20out%20of%20his%20retirement%20account%20to%20pay%20Old%20Republic%20off%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOld%20Republic%2C%20which%20also%20goes%20by%20the%20abbreviation%20ORNTIC%2C%20could%20not%20be%20reached%20for%20comment%2C%20however%20the%20company%20did%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kvoa.com%2Fnews%2Fn4t-investigators-property-sold-without-owners-knowledge-highlights-deed-fraud-risks%2Farticle_03c9821e-24f1-11ee-86a8-fb10ee153336.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemail%20a%20statement%20to%20Gordon's%20former%20legal%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20first%20reported%20by%20News%204%20Tucson%20in%20July%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BORNTIC%20has%20no%20contractual%20relationship%20with%20Mr.%20Gordon%20and%20declines%20to%20issue%20a%20title%20policy%20to%20Mr.%20Gordon.%C2%A0%20ORNTIC%20furthermore%20owes%20no%20duty%20of%20care%20to%20Mr.%20Gordon%20as%20ORNTIC%20was%20neither%20the%20escrow%20nor%20the%20title%20company%20handling%20this%20transaction.%C2%A0%20I%20understand%20that%20you%20allege%20that%20the%20escrow%20company%20failed%20to%20exercise%20due%20diligence%2C%20but%20that%20company%20is%20completely%20unrelated%20to%20ORNTIC.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20disturbed%20that%20this%20happened%20to%20him%2C%20but%2C%20he%20said%2C%20more%20upset%20with%20how%20little%20the%20title%20companies%20did%20to%20help%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20could%20have%20filed%20some%20paperwork%20with%20the%20county%2C%20reversed%20it%2C%20and%20all%20of%20this%20would've%20been%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20instead%20they%20made%20my%20life%20a%20living%20nightmare%20and%20then%20said%2C%20'Well%20it's%20not%20our%20responsibility.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmans-arizona-lot-sold-for-200000-without-him-listing-it-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692873901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e62b7b912f290019a9a320%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmans-arizona-lot-sold-for-200000-without-him-listing-it-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22William%20Gordon%20says%20his%20vacant%20Tucson%20property%20was%20fraudulently%20sold.%20He's%20spent%20over%20%249%2C000%20to%20get%20it%20back%2C%20and%20is%20left%20wondering%20how%20it%20happened.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmans-arizona-lot-sold-for-200000-without-him-listing-it-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dedollarization%20suffers%20a%20blow%20as%20the%20greenback's%20share%20in%20global%20payments%20hits%20a%20record%20high%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20employee%20of%20a%20bank%20counts%20US%20dollar%20notes%20at%20a%20branch%20in%20Hano