ou%20cannot%20trust%20the%20people%20you've%20hired%2C%20then%20maybe%20the%20best%20solution%20is%20for%20some%20type%20of%20oversight%20system%20where%20managers%20are%20walking%20around%20your%20desks%2C%26quot%3B%20Sam%20Eitzen%2C%20CEO%20of%20photo%20and%20video%20solutions%20company%20Snapbar%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-forever-boss-trust-employees-2023-8%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20just%20think%20that%20for%20me%2C%20that%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20a%20great%20long-term%20solution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStanford%20University%20economics%20professor%20Nicholas%20Bloom%20has%20reiterated%20that%20workers%20have%20kept%20up%20their%20productivity%20at%20home%2C%20citing%20data%20revealing%20the%20US%20is%20still%20on%20the%20pre-pandemic%20growth%20trend%20even%20with%20the%20number%20of%20remote%20workers%20quintupling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloom%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20opportunities%20for%20constructive%20leisure%20at%20home%20are%20much%20higher%20than%20in%20an%20office%2C%20which%20has%20led%20workers%20to%20take%20more%20profound%20breaks%20or%20do%20workouts%20to%20keep%20their%20minds%20fresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20studies%2C%20you%20see%20the%20valuation%20put%20on%20work%20from%20home%20is%20equivalent%20to%20about%20an%208%25%20pay%20increase%2C%20and%20the%20biggest%20driver%20of%20that%20is%20avoiding%20the%20commute%2C%20which%20is%20hardly%20surprising%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloom%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20second-biggest%20driver%20is%20flexibility%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20reflects%20the%20fact%20that%20breaks%20are%20just%20much%20more%20valuable%20at%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20businesses%20expect%20the%20current%20amount%20of%20remote%20work%20to%20continue%20into%20next%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York's%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorkfed.org%2Fmedialibrary%2Fmedia%2FSurvey%2Fbusiness_leaders%2F2023%2F2023_08Supplemental.pdf%3Fsc_lang%3Den%26hash%3DEBCDE1519D854626BAE55AF3DA282BF0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEmpire%20State%20Manufacturing%20Survey%20and%20Business%20Leaders%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Around%2017%25%20of%20service%20firms%20expect%20to%20require%20more%20in-person%20work%20next%20year%2C%20reporting%20declines%20in%20workplace%20culture%2C%20cohesiveness%2C%20communication%2C%20and%20training%20and%20mentoring%20of%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenvoy.com%2Fcontent%2Fdatareport%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20research%20from%20Envoy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2080%25%20of%20bosses%20regret%20their%20initial%20return-to-office%20plans%2C%20noting%20how%20they%20made%20these%20decisions%20without%20much%20awareness%20of%20office%20attendance%20and%20amenities%20usage.%20The%20risk%20of%20losing%20top%20talent%20has%20kept%20some%20companies%20on%20their%20toes%20about%20adopting%20stricter%20mandates%2C%20and%20the%20Envoy%20study%20further%20suggests%20a%20disconnect%20between%20what%20leaders%20and%20employees%20feel%20about%20return-to-office%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20to%20mention%2C%20mandatory%20return-to-office%20policies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-remote-work-from-home-commute-companies-climate-2023-8%5C%22%3Ecould%20exacerbate%20the%20climate%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20could%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20US%20economy%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20era%20of%20micromanagement%20is%20over%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20Done%20about%20five%20months%20to%20find%20a%20new%20job.%20He%20didn't%20want%20a%20hybrid%20or%20in-person%20position.%20With%20two%20kids%20at%20home%2C%20the%20flexibility%20of%20remote%20work%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0coupled%20with%20no%20commute%20%E2%