0and%20clear%20guidelines%20on%20the%20admissibility%20of%20dying%20declarations%20while%20acquitting%20a%20death-row%20convict%20by%20giving%20him%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20three-judge%20bench%2C%20comprising%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Prashant%20Kumar%20Mishra%2C%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2018%2F21899%2F21899_2018_14_1501_46308_Judgement_23-Aug-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIrfan%40Naka%20vs%20the%20State%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eheld%20that%20the%20court%20should%20always%20be%20on%20guard%20to%20see%20that%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20deceased%20was%20not%20a%20result%20of%20tutoring%20or%20prompting%20or%20a%20product%20of%20imagination.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20judgment%2C%20authored%20by%20Justice%20Pardiwala%2C%20came%20in%20a%20case%20in%20which%20a%20resident%20of%20Bijnore%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20was%20convicted%20of%20setting%20his%20son%20and%20two%20brothers%20on%20fire%20while%20they%20were%20sleeping%20%E2%80%93%20because%20of%20personal%20animosity.%20Both%20the%20Bijnore%20additional%20sessions%20judge%20and%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20had%20confirmed%20the%20conviction%20and%20death%20sentence%20of%20the%20appellant-convict.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20top%20court%20concluded%20that%20the%20prosecution%20was%20not%20able%20to%20prove%20beyond%20reasonable%20doubt%20that%20it%20was%20only%20and%20only%20the%20appellant-convict%20who%20set%20the%20room%20on%20fire%20by%20pouring%20an%20inflammable%20substance.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20dying%20declarations%20of%20two%20of%20the%20deceased%20%E2%80%93%20the%20convict%E2%80%99s%20son%20and%20one%20of%20his%20brothers%20%E2%80%93%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20the%20conviction%2C%20the%20judgment%20dives%20into%20the%20admissibility%20of%20such%20declarations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20justification%20for%20the%20sanctity%2Fpresumption%20attached%20to%20a%20dying%20declaration%20is%20two-fold%3A%20First%2C%20ethically%20and%20religiously%20it%20is%20presumed%20that%20a%20person%20while%20at%20the%20brink%20of%20death%20will%20not%20lie%2C%20and%20second%2C%20from%20a%20public%20policy%20perspective%20it%20is%20to%20tackle%20a%20situation%20where%20the%20only%20witness%20to%20the%20crime%20is%20not%20available.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bench%20held%20that%20dying%20declarations%2C%20while%20carrying%20a%20presumption%20of%20being%20true%2C%20must%20be%20wholly%20reliable%20and%20inspire%20confidence.%20Where%20there%20is%20any%20suspicion%20over%20the%20veracity%20of%20the%20same%20or%20the%20evidence%20on%20record%20shows%20that%20the%20dying%20declaration%20is%20not%20true%2C%20it%20will%20only%20be%20considered%20as%20a%20piece%20of%20evidence%20but%20cannot%20be%20the%20basis%20for%20conviction%20alone%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bench%20clarified%20that%20there%20is%20no%20hard%20and%20fast%20rule%20for%20determining%20when%20a%20dying%20declaration%20should%20be%20accepted.%20The%20duty%20of%20the%20court%20is%20to%20decide%20this%20question%20in%20the%20facts%20and%20surrounding%20circumstances%20of%20the%20case%20and%20be%20fully%20convinced%20of%20the%20truthfulness%20of%20the%20same.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECertain%20factors%20can%20be%20considered%20to%20determine%20the%20same%2C%20the%20bench%20held%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20will%20only%20affect%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20dying%20declaration%20and%20not%20its%20admissibility.%20These%20factors%2C%20the%20bench%20said%2C%20are%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(i)%20Whether%20the%20person%20making%20the%20statement%20was%20in%20expectation%20of%20death%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(ii)%20Whether%20the%20dying%20declaration%20was%20made%20at%20the%20earliest%20opportunity%3F%20%E2%80%9CRule%20of%20First%20Opportunity%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(iii)%20Whether%20there%20is%20any%20reasonable%20suspicion%20to%20believe%20the%20dying%20declaration%20was%20put%20in%20the%20mouth%20of%20the%20dying%20person%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(iv)%20Whether%20the%20dying%20declaration%20was%20a%20product%20of%20prompting%2C%20tutoring%20or%20leading%20at%20the%20instance%20of%20police%20or%20any%20interested%20party%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(v)%20Whether%20the%20statement%20was%20not%20recorded%20properly%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(vi)%20Whether%20the%20dying%20declarant%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20clearly%20observe%20the%20incident%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(vii)%20Whether%20the%20dying%20declaration%20has%20been%20consistent%20throughout%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(viii)%20Whether%20the%20dying%20declaration%20in%20itself%20is%20a%20manifestation%2Ffiction%20of%20the%20dying%20person%E2%80%99s%20imagination%20of%20what%20he%20thinks%20transpired%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(ix)%20Whether%20the%20dying%20declaration%20was%20itself%20voluntary%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E(x)%20Whether%2C%20as%20per%20the%20injuries%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20impossible%20for%20the%20deceased%20to%20make%20a%20dying%20declaration%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20the%20duty%20of%20the%20prosecution%20to%20establish%20the%20charge%20against%20the%20accused%20beyond%20a%20reasonable%20doubt%3B%20and%20the%20benefit%20of%20doubt%20must%20always%20be%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20the%20bench%20held.%20It%20is%20true%20that%20a%20dying%20declaration%20is%20a%20substantive%20piece%20of%20evidence%20to%20be%20relied%20on%20%E2%80%93%20provided%20it%20is%20also%20proved%20that%20the%20same%20was%20voluntary%20and%20truthful%20and%20the%20victim%20was%20in%20a%20fit%20state%20of%20mind.%20It%20is%20just%20not%20enough%20for%20the%20court%20to%20say%20that%20the%20dying%20declaration%20is%20reliable%20as%20the%20accused%20is%20named%20in%20the%20dying%20declaration%20as%20the%20assailant%2C%20the%20bench%20explained.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20unsafe%20to%20record%20the%20conviction%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20dying%20declaration%20alone%20in%20the%20cases%20where%20suspicion%2C%20like%20the%20case%20on%20hand%2C%20is%20raised%2C%20as%20regards%20the%20correctness%20of%20the%20dying%20declaration%2C%20the%20bench%20held.%20In%20such%20cases%2C%20the%20court%20may%20have%20to%20look%20for%20some%20corroborative%20evidence%20by%20treating%20the%20dying%20declaration%20only%20as%20a%20piece%20of%20evidence%3B%20the%20evidence%20and%20material%20available%20on%20record%20must%20be%20properly%20weighed%20in%20each%20case%20to%20arrive%20at%20an%20appropriate%20conclusion%2C%20the%20bench%20clarified.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reason%20why%20we%20say%20so%20is%20that%20in%20the%20case%20on%20hand%2C%20although%20the%20appellant-convict%20was%20named%20in%20two%20dying%20declarations%20as%20the%20person%20who%20set%20the%20room%20on%20fire%2C%20yet%20the%20surrounding%20circumstances%20render%20the%20statements%20of%20the%20declarants%20very%20doubtful%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20concluded.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20judgment%20cites%20the%201974%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F487684%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDharam%20Das%20Wadhwani%20vs%20State%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Everdict%20by%20Justice%20Krishna%20Iyer%2C%20which%20held%20that%20the%20rule%20of%20benefit%20of%20reasonable%20doubt%20does%20not%20imply%20a%20frail%20willow%20bending%20to%20every%20whiff%20of%20hesitancy.%20Judges%20are%20made%20of%20sterner%20stuff%20and%20must%20take%20a%20practical%20view%20of%20the%20legitimate%20inferences%20flowing%20from%20the%20evidence%2C%20circumstantial%20or%20direct.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20applying%20this%20principle%2C%20we%20have%20a%20doubt%20as%20regards%20the%20complicity%20of%20the%20appellant-convict%20in%20the%20crime%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20the%20order%20by%20Justice%20Pardiwala%20pointed%20out.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EProsecution%20Witness%5BPW%5D-2%20has%20been%20otherwise%20also%20not%20believed%20by%20the%20High%20Court.%C2%A0%20It%20is%20difficult%20to%20rest%20the%20conviction%20solely%20based%20on%20the%20two%20dying%20declarations.%C2%A0%20The%20oral%20evidence%20of%20the%20PW-4%20Soni%20also%20does%20not%20inspire%20any%20confidence%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20further%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18150906%2FSupreme-Court.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18150906%2FSupreme-Court.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18150906%2FSupreme-Court-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18150906%2FSupreme-Court-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-653640%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Credit%3A%20Subhashish%20Panigrahi%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC%20by%20SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFacts%20of%20the%20case%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20appellant-convict%20was%20married%20twice.%20The%20first%20marriage%20was%20with%20a%20lady%2C%20who%20was%20the%20daughter%20of%20his%20uncle%20(PW-1).%20His%20second%20marriage%20was%20solemnised%20with%20another%20lady.%20One%20son%20by%20the%20name%20of%20Islamuddin%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20killed%20in%20the%20fire%20%E2%80%93%20was%20born%20in%20wedlock%20with%20his%20first%20wife.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20convict%20had%20two%20brothers%2C%20namely%2C%20Irshad%20and%20Naushad%20%E2%80%93%20both%20of%20whom%20were%20also%20killed%20%E2%80%93%20and%20who%20lived%20along%20with%20him%20and%20his%20sister%20Soni%20(PW-4).%20Another%20brother%20by%20the%20name%20Shanu%20alias%20Shahnawaz%20(PW-2)%20of%20the%20convict%20lived%20in%20the%20neighbourhood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20prosecution%2C%20the%20three%20deceased%20persons%20more%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20Islamuddin%20(the%20convict%E2%80%99s%20son)%20%E2%80%93%20were%20highly%20opposed%20to%20the%20second%20marriage%20of%20the%20appellant-convict.%20Islamuddin%20was%20even%20once%20beaten%20by%20the%20appellant-convict%20as%20he%20had%20offered%20a%20lot%20of%20opposition%20to%20the%20second%20marriage%20of%20his%20father.%20The%20two%20deceased%20brothers%20had%20also%20defended%20Islamuddin%E2%80%99s%20opposition%20to%20the%20second%20marriage%20of%20the%20appellant%2C%20the%20prosecution%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20August%206%2C%202014%2C%20at%20around%2012%3A30%20am%2C%20the%20PW-2%20%E2%80%93%20another%20brother%20of%20the%20convict%20%E2%80%93%20is%20said%20to%20have%20woken%20up%20to%20see%20flames%20and%20smoke%20coming%20from%20the%20room%20where%20the%20deceased%20persons%20were%20sleeping.%20The%20PW-2%20and%20his%20sister%20Soni%20(PW-4)%20claim%20to%20have%20seen%20the%20appellant-convict%20setting%20the%20room%20on%20fire%20and%20thereafter%2C%20fastening%20the%20door%20latch%20from%20outside%20and%20running%20away.%20While%20PW-4%20lives%20in%20the%20same%20house%20as%20the%20convict%2C%20PW-2%20claimed%20he%20was%20there%20to%20have%20dinner%20with%20PW-4%20and%20the%20deceased%20persons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20prosecution%20claimed%20that%20the%20PW-2%20and%20PW-4%20opened%20their%20doors%20and%20saw%20the%20appellant-convict%20running%20from%20the%20roof%20towards%20the%20stairs.%20According%20to%20the%20case%20of%20the%20prosecution%2C%20two%20other%20persons%20%E2%80%93%20who%20were%20not%20examined%20%E2%80%93%20also%20saw%20the%20appellant-convict%20running%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%2023%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20find%20it%20very%20difficult%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20appellant-convict%20was%20still%20inside%20the%20room%20or%20even%20outside%20the%20room%20to%20be%20witnessed%20by%20the%20deceased%20persons%20as%20well%20as%20by%20the%20PW-2%20and%20PW-4%2C%20locking%20the%20room%20from%20outside%20after%20setting%20the%20room%20on%20fire%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20bench%2C%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20accused%20might%20be%20%E2%80%9Cunnatural%E2%80%9D%20but%20such%20conduct%2C%20which%20may%20be%20a%20relevant%20factor%20under%20Section%208%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20%E2%80%9Cby%20itself%20may%20not%20be%20sufficient%20to%20hold%20a%20person%20guilty%20of%20the%20offence%20of%20murder%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHad%20the%20dying%20declarations%20stood%20corroborated%20by%20the%20oral%20evidence%20of%20PW-2%20and%20PW-4%2C%20then%20probably%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20altogether%20a%20different%20scenario.%20However%2C%20the%20bench%20found%20that%20the%20two%20dying%20declarations%20were%20not%20consistent%20or%20rather%20contradictory%20to%20the%20oral%20evidence%20on%20record.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692865771000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F14145256%2Fgavel_pixabay.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-guidelines-admissibility-dying-declarations%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20three-judge%20bench%20held%20that%20courts%20should%20always%20be%20on%20guard%20to%20see%20that%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20deceased%20was%20not%20a%20result%20of%20tutoring%20or%20prompting%20or%20a%20product%20of%20imagination.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-guidelines-admissibility-dying-declarations%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22R%20Praggnanandhaa%3A%20Not%20Just%20A%20Wonderkid%2C%20But%20A%20Great%20In%20The%20Making%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFor%20someone%2C%20who%20took%20to%20chess%20just%20because%20his%20parents%20wanted%20him%20and%20his%20sister%20to%20wean%20away%20from%20watching%20television%2C%20R%20Praggnanandhaa%20has%20charted%20his%20own%20path%20to%20glory%20and%20is%20closer%20to%20greatness%20than%20ever.%20The%2018-year%20old%20wonderboy%20has%20long%20been%20seen%20as%20a%20possible%20successor%20to%20the%20five-time%20world%20champion%20Viswanathan%20Anand%20and%20is%20certainly%20on%20the%20path%20to%20be%20a%20chess%20great.%20A%20stunning%20performance%20in%20the%20FIDE%20World%20Cup%20in%20Baku%20has%20catapulted%20him%20to%20the%20Candidates%20tournament%20to%20determine%20the%20challenger%20to%20current%20world%20champion%20Ding%20Liren.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20becoming%20the%20only%20Indian%20player%20after%20Anand%20to%20book%20a%20spot%20in%20the%20Candidates%2C%20the%20Chennai%20teenager%20has%20proved%20that%20he%20will%20be%20the%20name%20to%20reckon%20with%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20big-ticket%20chess%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20wonderkid%2C%20who%20took%20up%20the%20sport%20at%20the%20age%20of%20four-and-a-half%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%20has%20achieved%20several%20firsts%20in%20his%20distinguished%20career%20thus%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20coming%20under%20the%20wings%20of%20Anand%2C%20who%20has%20taken%20to%20mentorship%20like%20a%20duck%20to%20water%2C%20the%20rise%20has%20been%20steady%20for%20Praggnanandhaa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20beating%20Magnus%20Carlsen%2C%20the%20world%20No.1%20and%20former%20classical%20champion%20in%20an%20online%20tournament%20last%20year%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%20showed%20that%20he%20could%20soak%20in%20the%20pressure%20and%20defeat%20the%20best%20in%20the%20business%20at%20their%20own%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20questions%20remain%20on%20his%20ability%20in%20the%20classical%20format%2C%20the%20teenaged%20GM%20has%20shown%20that%20he%20has%20it%20in%20him%20to%20be%20in%20the%20big%20league.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHailing%20from%20Chennai%2C%20the%20hotspot%20of%20Indian%20chess%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%20has%20been%20in%20the%20spotlight%20since%20he%20made%20waves%20at%20a%20young%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20won%20the%20national%20under-7%20title%20to%20lay%20down%20the%20marker%20and%20has%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20ever%20since.%20At%2010%2C%20he%20was%20an%20International%20Master%20and%20two%20years%20later%2C%20he%20became%20a%20GM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELate%20in%202019%2C%20he%20achieved%20a%20ELO%20rating%20of%202600%20at%2014%20years%20and%20three%20months%20and%20looked%20to%20be%20on%20the%20overdrive.%20The%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%202020%20came%20as%20a%20speed%20bump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%20shone%20in%20online%20tournaments%20and%20kept%20getting%20better.%20In%202021%2C%20he%20impressed%20in%20the%20Meltwater%20Champions%20Tour%2C%20scoring%20victories%20over%20top%20names%20like%20Sergey%20Karjakin%2C%20Teimour%20Radjabov%20and%20Jan-Krzystof%20Duda%20and%20drawing%20Carlsen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20his%20stock%20rose%20further%20when%20he%20stunned%20Carlsen%20in%20the%20Airthings%20Masters%20rapid%20tournament.%20He%20became%20only%20the%20third%20Indian%20after%20Anand%20and%20P%20Harikrishna%20to%20win%20a%20game%20against%20the%20seemingly%20unbeatable%20Carlsen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPraggnanandhaa's%20calm%20demeanour%20when%20at%20the%20table%20hides%20a%20confident%20and%20aggressive%20player.%20He%20can%20be%20quite%20a%20formidable%20opponent%20when%20he%20sits%20across%20the%20table%20for%20a%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20he%20has%20shown%20great%20fighting%20qualities%2C%20in%20the%20World%20Cup%20especially.%20Up%20against%20world%20No.2%20Hikaru%20Nakamura%2C%20he%20showed%20that%20in%20abundance%20and%20felled%20a%20higher-rated%20opponent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20against%20Fabiano%20Caruana%2C%20the%20world%20No.3%2C%20in%20the%20semifinal%2C%20his%20defensive%20capabilities%20were%20to%20the%20fore%20and%20he%20came%20through%20in%20a%20nerve-wracking%20tie-break.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Grandmaster%20M%20Shyam%20Sundar%2C%20a%20coach%20with%20the%20Indian%20team%20in%20Baku%20for%20the%20World%20Cup%2C%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20his%20(Praggnanandhaa's)%20biggest%20strengths%20is%20his%20ability%20to%20defend%20bad%20positions%20even%20against%20the%20absolute%20elite.%26quot%3B%20This%20stands%20him%20in%20good%20stead%20in%20adverse%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20apart%2C%20as%20Shyam%20Sundar%20says%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%20is%20good%20in%20all%20formats%20and%20that%20helped%20him%20reach%20the%20finals%20as%20he%20was%20confident%20in%20the%20tie-breaks%20against%20Caruana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20Anand%2C%20family%20support%2C%20especially%20from%20his%20mother%2C%20has%20been%20a%20great%20factor%20in%20his%20evolution%20as%20a%20player.%20His%20mother%20Nagalakshmi%20is%20a%20constant%20at%20tournaments%20that%20he%20plays%20and%20he%20seems%20to%20feed%20off%20her%20valuable%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20feeling%20that%20Praggnanandhaa's%20opening%20repertoire%20is%20not%20top-notch%20but%20he%20is%20quite%20a%20force%20in%20the%20rapid%20and%20blitz%20formats%20and%20in%20online%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20improved%20leaps%20and%20bounds%20and%20with%20the%20work%20put%20in%20under%20noted%20coach%20R%20B%20Ramesh%20and%20subsequently%20Anand%20(as%20the%20mentor)%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%20can%20only%20get%20better%2C%20which%20may%20not%20be%20good%20news%20for%20his%20rivals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20achieved%20a%20lot%20at%2018%20and%20is%20already%20on%20the%20path%20to%20greatness.%20With%20people%20of%20the%20stature%20of%20Anand%20and%20Ramesh%20to%20guide%20him%2C%20the%20Chennai%20player%20will%20be%20dreaming%20of%20becoming%20the%20world%20champion%20sooner%20than%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20someone%20so%20talented%2C%20Praggnanandhaa%2C%20surprisingly%2C%20is%20yet%20to%20win%20the%20national%20championship%20despite%20his%20other%20accomplishments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20performance%20in%20the%20FIDE%20World%20Cup%20has%20turned%20the%20spotlight%20firmly%20on%20him%20even%20as%20compatriots%20like%20D%20Gukesh%20and%20Arjun%20Erigaisi%20too%20has%20kept%20reminding%20the%20chess%20world%20of%20their%20own%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20triumph%20against%20Carlsen%20would%20certainly%20help%20Praggnanandhaa%20pull%20away%20from%20the%20two%20ambitious%20fellow%20Indians%20and%20on%20the%20way%20to%20achieving%20his%20dream%20of%20fighting%20for%20the%20world%20title%20by%20contesting%20the%20Candidates%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692865140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fasa1opeo_r-praggnanandhaa_625x300_22_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fchess%2Fr-praggnanandha